<p>By submitting content to the GSW platform for <em>Lithosphere</em>, contributors agree to license their submissions and to public under CC-BY 4.0 license and other terms specified by GSW. This includes any content submitted by third party vendor. <em>Lithosphere</em> is a Gold Open Access publication. Authors, their employers, or research funders pay an author publication charge (APC), currently of US $2,200 but subject to change, plus any applicable mandator page charges. APCs may typically be paid by employers or research funding agencies and, if by the author, from a portion of author’s research funds designated for open-access publishing. The fee applies to all journal articles. Submission information can be found at <a href="https://pubs.geoscienceworld.org/lithosphere/pages/about-lithosphere" target="_self">oa.geoscienceworld.org</a> or by emailing <a href="mailto:editorial@geoscienceworld.org">editorial@geoscienceworld.org</a>.</p>
<p>For ethical guidelines covering submissions to <em>Lithosphere</em>, GSW is a member of <a href="https://publicationethics.org," target="_blank">the Committee on Publication Ethics</a> and supports and abides by those guidelines. All submitting authors must agree upon submission to adhere to these guidelines as well. Any action deemed to be in conflict with these guideline may result in punitive action on behalf the GSW editorial staff up to and including refusing publication of any additional submissions for 5 years at minimum.</p>



 
